Fuction
  - a block of code designed to particular task
  - executed whebn "something" invokes/calls it
  ________________
  2 ways to create a function
    - function declaration
    - function expression
  _______________
  Function declaration
  
  function calculateArea (width,height) {
    let area(width * height);
    return area 
    }
    
      function //keyword
      calculateArea //indentifier/name of function
      (width, height) //parameters
      {} //function of body or block of statement to perform a specific task
      (width * height) //parameters treated as variables
      return //keyword
        - stops the execution of function
        - returns a value from that function
      area //return area
    
    console.log(calculateArea(10,6));
    
    calculateArea() //executes the the code
      (10,6) Parameters' aruguements as value   
 _________________
 Fuction Expression
 
 const calculateArea=function(width,height0 {
    const area= width*height;
    return area;
 };
 
 calculateArea //indentifier
 function //keyword& anonymous function
___________________
Arrow function
  -shorthand version of function
  
=> //to replace function

zero Parameters
  const functionName=()=> {};
one Parameter
  const functionName = paramOne => {};
two or more parameters
  const functionName = (paramOne, paraTwo) => {};
  
single-line block
  const sumNumbers = number => number + number;
multi-line Block
   const sumNumbers = number => {
      const sum = number + number;
      return sum;
    };
    
    
